HEADWORD: Divi-divi
<hw>Di"vi-di"vi</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Native
name.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A small tree of tropical America
(<spn>C⟦ae⟧salpinia coriaria</spn>), whose legumes contain a large
proportion of tannic and gallic acid, and are used by tanners and
dyers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

